cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on the application of checkpoint ensembles to neural networks, which is a popular topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses three real-world datasets, including text and image data, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses regularization techniques, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
